RABIES, RACCOONS, VACCINES (06)
===============================
[see: Rabies, raccoons, vaccines (04) 970522180713
Rabies, raccoons - vaccines (02) 970519155144
Rabies, raccoons - vaccines (03) 970520125440
Rabies, raccoons - vaccines: RFI 970517174911]
[1]
Date: Fri, 23 May 1997 11:35:03 -0400
From: Terry Whiting <twhiting@EM.AGR.CA>

Vaccination is not universally innocuous.
There has been some laboratory models of increased pathogenicity of
rabies street virus infection in newly vaccinated animals. It is referred to
as "early death" (Sikes R.W. et al Bull. WHO, 45:1, 1971). Low levels of
antibody in the post vaccination window may increase susceptibility to
challenge with street virus.
This may have no effect in this field application; but, without testing we
do not know. We are dealing with an enzootic fatal zoonosis.
References
Blancou J., Andral B., and Andral L.,
A model in mice for the study of the early death phenomenon after
vaccination and challenge with rabies virus
J, gen, Virol. (1980). 50. 433-435
Prabhakar BS, & Nathanson N
Acute rabies death mediated by antibody
Nature Vol 290 16 April 1891 pp590
